<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.91.83091.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Jenniferia griseocinerea a fungus on a spider (BBH 29656) b perithecium c asci d ascus tip e, f whole ascospores with septate part-spores alternately connected with thread-like structures g fungus on a spider (BBH 33219) h short synnema i long synnema j phialides k conidia l, m colonies on OA at 21 days (l obverse, m reverse) n, o colonies on PDA at 21 days (n obverse, o reverse). Scale bars: 2 mm (a, g); 200 µm (b); 100 µm (c, h, i); 10 µm (d, e, f, j, k)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719479" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/mycokeys.91.83091.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. RAxML tree of Hevansia, Jenniferia, Parahevasia, Polystromomyces and related genera in the Cordycipitaceae from a combined ITS, LSU, tef 1, rpb 1 and rpb 2 dataset. Numbers at the major nodes represent Maximum Likelihood Bootstrap (MLB) and Bayesian Posterior Probabilities (BPP). Bold lines in the tree represent 100 % of MLB and 1.00 of BPP. Symbols on the right-hand side correspond to the types of ascospore morphologies found in each genus that are observed in natural specimens of Cordycipitaceae described in Fig. 2." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719474" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

